<CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Hoof it on over to the California State Horseman's Association
parade at 10 a.m. on Saturday in Newark, part of the Newark Days Celebration.  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  FAMILY; RECREATION  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  ART is getting an outing with a few festivals to celebrate Bay Area works. The
36th annual Newark Days Celebration will be Thursday through next Sunday. A
highlight of the celebration is the Newark Days Fine Arts Show, where arts and
crafts will be display. Also at the festival will be entertainment, contests,
stage shows, storytellers, a carnival and appearances by Ninja Turtle
Michaelangelo and Little Red Riding Hood. A hundred horses will be trotted out
at the California State Horseman's Association championship parade at 10 a.m.
on Saturday, from Newark Boulevard to Cedar Street. The festival is at Newark
Community Center, 35501 Cedar Blvd., Newark. Admission is free. For more
information, call (415) 793-5683.;   Another arts affair is on today, the San
Carlos Festival of the Arts, which features continuous entertainment and, of
course, arts and crafts. The festival is 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at City Hall Park,
San Carlos Avenue and Elm Street, San Carlos. Admission is free. A parade,
starting at Laurel Street and heading toward the park, will be at 10 a.m.
(415) 593-0061.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  GET OUTSIDE AND SEE THE ARTS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The Family Clipboard; Things to do  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     And the Santa Cruz County Fair is celebrating its 50th anniversary,
featuring exhibits, animals, contests, continuous entertainment and a
carnival. Noon to 11 p.m. Tuesday through Wednesday, 10 a.m. to 11 p.m.
Thursday, and 10 a.m. to midnight next Friday, Santa Cruz County Fairgrounds,
2601 E. Lake Ave., Watsonville. Through next Sunday. Admission is $6 adults,
$3.50 children ages 5 to 11, $3 seniors. (408) 724-5671.;   Exhibits; Bay Area
Discovery Museum.  Hands-on, interactive museum designed for children ages 2
to 12. Exhibits on San Francisco Bay marine life, history and architecture,
plus an art studio, cafe and picnic area. 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Tuesdays-Sundays,
557 E. Fort Baker, Sausalito (Alexander Avenue off-ramp from Hwy. 101 north
across Golden Gate Bridge). $5 adults, $4 seniors, $3 children, under 2 free.
(415) 332-9646.;   Children's Discovery Museum  Hours are noon to 5 p.m.
today, then closed from Sept. 9 to 23. Thereafter, fall hours will be: 10 a.m.
to 5 p.m. Tuesdays-Saturdays and noon to 5 p.m. Sundays. School groups must
book in advance. The museum features hands-on interactive exhibits and
programs. Located at Woz Way and Auzerais Street, San Jose. $6 adults, $3
children (ages 4-18), ages 3 and under free. (408) 298-5437.;   The
Exploratorium.  Hands-on science museum. 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Tuesdays-Sundays;
10 a.m. to 9:30 p.m. Wednesdays. Closed Mondays, except holidays. $7 general,
$5 students, $3.50 seniors, $3 disabled, $3 youth (ages 6-17), $2 children
(ages 6-11), free to under 6. Tactile Dome open Tuesdays-Sundays, $7 per
person (includes museum admission). Call (415) 561-0362 for Tactile Dome
reservations. Palace of Fine Arts, 3601 Lyon St. General information: (415)
561-0360. Performance/lecture hot line: (415) 561-0361.;   Lawrence Hall of
Science.  Reduced admission month. Attractions include 30-foot robotic
apatosaurus, hands-on exhibits including "Within the Human Brain," computer
games, "Laser, the Light Fantastic" show. 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. daily. Located
at UC-Berkeley. Through Sept. 29, admission is $2, $1 seniors, children and
students. Children under 7 free. Regular adult admission ($4) resumes Sept.
30. (415) 642-5132.;   Sharks.  This special exhibit exploring the myths and
realities of sharks continues at the Monterey Bay Aquarium through Oct. 20.
The exhibit features live species, hands-on activities and video
presentations. It is free with regular aquarium admission of $9 adults, $6.50
students and seniors, and $4 children (ages 3-12). Sea otters, touch pool and
a three-story kelp forest are all regular exhibits at the aquarium, 886
Cannery Row, Monterey. Open daily 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. (408) 648-4888.;   Viewing
of the Moon Festival.  Japanese celebration. Handmade character dolls,
Japanese arts, music. 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. today, Post Street between Fillmore
and Laguna. Free. (415) 346-4446.;   Upcoming; Kid Safe Saturday.  For
youngsters ages 5-14. First aid, CPR demonstrations, fingerprinting, baby
sitters' workshop, file/electrical safety, "This Is Me," personal safety,
making emergency calls, drug abuse. Classes are held on the hour and
half-hour. By Community Hospital and Rehabilitation Center. 10 a.m. to 3 p.m.
Sept. 21, 815 Pollard Road, Los Gatos. (408) 866-4058.;   San Francisco
Children's Opera.  "Sleeping Beauty," Nov. 23; "A Date With Santa," Dec. 21;
"The Emperor's New Clothes," Feb. 1; "Sinbad the Sailor," March 14; "Snow
White and Rose Red," April 25. Herbst Theater, San Francisco. Season tickets
only. $35-$70. (415) 386-9622.  </TEXT>
